This was another happy discovery, and a nice place to stop in for old-fashioned Spanish comfort food.  My favorite dish from here is the garlic chicken with rice and beans, as well as the fresh juices.  One can make a dish off of the snack foods and smaller dishes by themselves; the standard rice platter that came with the aforementioned chicken lasted me for a few days, there was so much.  They also have a wide variety of breakfast dishes and don't mind customizing them as needed.
